[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_6lr4b")
reagent_id = "Na2CO3"
title = "Sodium carbonate"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]Na₂CO₃[/cell]
[cell]Common name:[/cell][cell]Soda ash / Washing soda[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]106 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
2NaOH + CO₂ → Na₂CO₃ + H₂O  
2Na + H₂CO₃ → Na₂CO₃ + H₂  
2NaOH + H₂CO₃ → Na₂CO₃ + 2H₂O  
Na₂O + CO₂ → Na₂CO₃  
Na₂O + H₂CO₃ → Na₂CO₃ + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound.  
• Soluble in water, forming an alkaline solution.  
• Reacts with acids to produce carbon dioxide.
[b]Where sodium carbonate is found[/b]
• In some natural mineral deposits (trona).  
• Produced industrially by the Solvay process.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Glass production.  
• Detergents and cleaning products.  
• Water softening.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can irritate skin and eyes in concentrated form."
